  "AICL is the licensing and transaction layer built on top of AICR. Where AICR declares what is allowed, AICL defines how permission is actually obtained: license tiers and prices, quote and payment endpoints, signed license tokens, usage and audit logs, and revocation. It is designed to interoperate with emerging machine-payment mechanisms such as HTTP 402 flows and pay-per-crawl schemes, with agentic payment kept inside human-approved budgets and audit trails.": "AICL ke lera la dilaesense le dikgwebo le hahilweng holim'a AICR. Moo AICR e bolelang seo se dumeletsweng, AICL e hlalosa mokgwa oo tumello e fumanwang ka wona: mekgahlelo le ditheko tsa dilaesense, li-endpoint tsa tlhahiso ya theko le tefo, li-token tsa laesense tse saenilweng, direkoto tsa tshebediso le tlhahlobo, le ho hlakola. E entswe hore e sebedisane le mekgwa e ntjha ya tefo ya mochini e kang metsamao ya HTTP 402 le mekgwa ya pay-per-crawl, moo tefo ya di-agent e bolokwang ka hare ho ditekanyetso tse dumeletsweng ke motho le direkoto tsa tlhahlobo.",
