  "Convert rights declarations into a workable licensing market instead of a binary open/closed web.": "Fetola diboitsebiso tsa litokelo hore e be mmaraka wa dilaesense o sebetsang, ho e-na le Web e le nngwe kapa tjhe e bulehileng kapa e koetsweng.",
  "Copied ✓": "E Kopilwe ✓",
  "Copy": "Kopa",
  "Correct positioning: independent research drafts, protocol proposals, and an open specification experiment.": "Boemo bo Nepahetseng: meralo e ikemetseng ya dipatlisiso, ditlhahiso tsa diprotokolo, le teko e bulehileng ya ditlhaloso.",
  "Corrected an earlier default: Belgium (BE) now maps to Dutch instead of French — Flemish speakers are the country’s majority (~60%) over Walloon French speakers (~40%).": "Ho lokisitswe kgetho ya kgale: Belgium (BE) hona jwale e lebisa ho Sedatshe ho e-na le Sefora — babuwi ba Seflemishe ke boholo ba naha (~60%) ho feta babuwi ba Sefora ba Walloon (~40%).",
  "Corrected an earlier default: Kazakhstan (KZ) now maps to Kazakh instead of Russian, now that a Kazakh translation exists — the same kind of fix as the earlier Belgium correction.": "Ho lokisitswe kgetho ya kgale: Kazakhstan (KZ) hona jwale e lebisa ho Sekazakh ho e-na le Serashea, hona hobane hona jwale ho na le phetolelo ya Sekazakh — ke mofuta o tshwanang wa tokiso jwaloka tokiso ya pele ya Belgium.",
  "Could AI Be Conscious?": "Could AI Be Conscious?",
  "Crawler access rules": "Melawana ya Phihlello ya Crawler",
  "Crawler simulator": "Simulator ya Crawler",
  "Currency": "Tjhelete",
  "Custom tier": "Mokgahlelo o Entsweng ka Boo",
  "Daily Nous reports on a retracted Journal of Medical Ethics submission containing multiple fabricated, AI-hallucinated references — complete with fake university affiliations and defunct email addresses — that the author reportedly left uncorrected even after being given a chance to fix proofs. The piece contrasts this with Bioethics, whose automated reference-checking would have caught the problem, and argues the real bottleneck isn't detection technology (one commenter's script flagged the fake citations in under a minute) but unpaid reviewer labor and publishing incentives that reward throughput over scrutiny.": "Daily Nous e tlaleha ka tokomane e hlakotsweng ho Journal of Medical Ethics e neng e na le diphetiso tse ngata tse thehilweng, tse entsweng ke AI ka boitsiso — hammoho le dikamano tsa mahaeng tsa maiketsetso le diaterese tsa email tse sa sebetseng — tseo mongodi a ileng a di siya di sa lokiswa esita le kamora ho fuwa monyetla wa ho lokisa diprofo. Sengoloa se bapisa sena le Bioethics, moo tlhahlobo ya diphetiso e itiretseng e neng e tla fumana bothata boo, mme se bolela hore bothata ba nnete hase theknoloji ya ho fumana (script ya mohlahluoi e mong e ile ya lemoha diqotsiso tsa maiketsetso ka nako e ka tlase ho motsotso), empa ke mosebetsi o sa lefelloang wa bahlahlobi le meputso ya ho phatlalatsa e putsang bongata ho feta tlhokomelo.",
  "Data free-riding vs. trillion-dollar AI valuations": "Ho Sebedisa Data ka Mahala nakong eo Boleng ba AI bo Lekantsweng ka Ditrilione",
  "DeepMind CEO calls for an independent standards body to regulate frontier AI": "DeepMind CEO calls for an independent standards body to regulate frontier AI",
  "Demis Hassabis proposed a FINRA-style regulator for frontier model releases: labs would submit models for review up to 30 days before deployment, voluntary at first, with a path toward mandatory compliance in the US market.": "Demis Hassabis o sisintse molaodi wa mofuta wa FINRA bakeng sa tokollo ya dimmotlolo tse hodimo: dilaboratori di tla romella dimmotlolo tsa tlhahlobo matsatsi a ka bang 30 pele di tsebiswa setjhabeng, e le ka boithatelo qalong, ka tsela e isang ho kgapeletso mmarakeng wa US.",
  "Denied": "Ho Hanetswe",
  "Deployable policy starter template": "Teplete ya Qalo ya Leano e Kgonang ho Sebediswa",
  "Deployable policy starter template at /downloads/agiright-policy-starter.zip — a minimal static site with the full machine-readable layer, ready for Cloudflare Pages or any static host.": "Teplete ya qalo ya leano e kgonang ho sebediswa e fumaneha ho /downloads/agiright-policy-starter.zip — sebaka se tsitsitseng se se nyane se nang le lera le felletseng le balehang ke mochini, se lokiseditswe Cloudflare Pages kapa sebaka leha e le sefe se tsitsitseng.",
  "Deploying machine-readable policies on your site": "Ho Kenya Maano a Balehang ke Mochini Sebakeng sa Hao",
  "Disclaimer": "Temoso",
  "Distinct from human UI, SEO, or plain APIs, the AI Ingestion & Capability Layer gives websites a machine-facing architecture: a Manifest Layer (entry points like /llms.txt and /ai/manifest.json), a Corpus Layer (machine-readable knowledge), a Capability Layer (agent-callable tools), and a Governance Layer (provenance, licensing, versioning). Static-first, upgradeable toward APIs and MCP. Note: in this paper AICL names the ingestion architecture; on this site's protocol pages AICL refers to the AI Content Licensing Layer.": "Ka phapano le UI ya batho, SEO, kapa di-API tse tlwaelehileng, AI Ingestion & Capability Layer e fa disebaka tsa marang-rang moaho o shebaneng le mechini: Lera la Manifest (dibaka tsa ho kena tse kang /llms.txt le /ai/manifest.json), Lera la Corpus (tsebo e balehang ke mochini), Lera la Bokgoni (disebediswa tse ka bitswang ke agent), le Lera la Taolo (mohlodi wa tsebo, dilaesense, livesene). E qala e le e tsitsitseng, e ka ntlafatswa ho ea ho di-API le MCP. Hlokomela: pampiring ena AICL e bitsa moralo ona wa ho kenya diteng; maqepheng a diprotokolo a sebaka sena AICL e bolela Lera la Dilaesense tsa Diteng tsa AI.",
  "Do Large Language Models Possess a Theory of Mind? A Comparative Evaluation Using the Strange Stories Paradigm": "Do Large Language Models Possess a Theory of Mind? A Comparative Evaluation Using the Strange Stories Paradigm",
  "Docs": "Ditokomane",
  "Docs / Examples": "Ditokomane / Mehlala",
  "Document library": "Laebrari ya Ditokomane",
  "Does AI have rights — and which framings are even coherent?": "Na AI e na le litokelo — mme na mekgwa efe ya ho hlalosa taba ena e utlwahalang?",
  "Download": "Kgothaletsa",
  "Draft status": "Boemo ba Moralo",
  "EU AI Act: What Actually Applies on 2 August 2026": "EU AI Act: What Actually Applies on 2 August 2026",
  "Educational demo: HMAC-SHA256 with a shared secret, showing request-bound, expiring, verifiable license tokens. Production tokens should be signed asymmetrically, with the publisher’s public key discoverable under /.well-known/.": "Ponyo ya thuto: HMAC-SHA256 e sebedisang sephiri se arolelanwang, e bontshang di-token tsa laesense tse tlamanang le kopo, tse felang ke nako, mme tse ka netefatswang. Di-token tsa tshebetso ya sebele di lokela ho saenwa ka mokgwa o sa lekaneng (asymmetrically), moo senotlolo sa phatlalatso sa mophatlalatsi se ka fumanwang tlasa /.well-known/.",
  "Eight more /topics entries, this time researched by an AI agent rather than curated by hand — same rule as before: every source fetched and confirmed live, summaries an original paraphrase, before anything gets added. 14 entries total.": "Diteng tse ding tse robedi ho /topics, lekgetlong lena di ile tsa fuputswa ke agent ya AI ho e-na le ho kgethwa ka letsoho — molao o tshwanang le pele: mohlodi o mong le o mong o ile wa fumanwa mme wa netefatswa o sebetsa, dikakaretso ke tlhaloso ya rona ya mantlha, pele ho kenngwa letho. Kakaretso ke diteng tse 14.",
  "Email": "Imeile",
  "Emotion Concepts and Their Function in a Large Language Model": "Emotion Concepts and Their Function in a Large Language Model",
  "Empirical Research": "Dipatlisiso tse Thehilweng Diphuputsong",
  "English edition →": "Kgatiso ya Senyesemane →",
